To mitigate this risk, you should use a more robust parsing mechanism that handles different types of delimiters and ensures that only valid data is processed. Here's an example of how you can modify the code to handle different delimiters and ensure that only numeric values are used:

```java
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class OrderProcessor {
    private Map<String, Integer> priceList = new HashMap<>();

    public void addProduct(String productName, int price) {
        priceList.put(productName, price);
    }

    public int calculateTotalPrice(String orderString) {
        // Split the order string by a delimiter that is unlikely to be present in the order data
        String[] orderData = orderString.split("\\|");

        if (orderData.length != 2) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid order format");
        }

        String productDetails = orderData[0];
        int quantity = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]);

        // Split the product details by a delimiter that is unlikely to be present in the product name
        String[] parts = productDetails.split("\\s+");

        if (parts.length != 2) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid product format");
        }

        String productName = parts[0];
        int price = Integer.parseInt(parts[1]);

        // Check if the product exists in the price list
        if (!priceList.containsKey(productName)) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Product not found in price list");
        }

        // Calculate the total price
        int orderPrice = quantity * priceList.get(productName);

        return orderPrice;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        OrderProcessor processor = new OrderProcessor();
        processor.addProduct("Apple", 1.50);
        processor.addProduct("Banana", 0.75);

        String orderString = "Apple|2";
        int totalPrice = processor.calculateTotalPrice(orderString);
        System.out.println("Total price: $" + totalPrice);
    }
}
```

In this modified code, we use a delimiter like `|` that is unlikely to be present in the order data. We also split the product details by a delimiter like ` ` (space) that is unlikely to be present in the product name. This ensures that only valid data is processed and prevents injection attacks.

